caption: Bring your hunger - portions are large. Like a restaurant in Washington I liked.
came in on a thurs. will surely make a return trip. the bill was fair for the quality of food.
Staff was very polite and friendly.

First off I’d like to say that Eddy gave us the best service of all time, give that man a day to play whatever records he wants to bring in.  Exceptional and delicious. I got the breakfast burrito with the in house cured bacon, no cheese. Eddy was on top of my lactose sensitive, no cheese in my burrito and oat milk in my coffee. The service was detailed and on point!  My boyfriend had the French toast, phenomenal. We indulged in the two varieties of doughnuts of the day, well worth it.  We got there shortly after 10am on Saturday, we were the only ones there for a while, great start to our day at the museum.
Management and service staff are amazing, and so as food. We had a great time and felt undivided attention from the staff!
Fabulous restaurant in the Museum of Contemporary Art lower level.  The service was excellent and the seasonal menu was filled with unique choices.   Prices were not outrageous.

Awesome option for a Sunday brunch! The menu has very interesting options - the pork cheek ragout was delicious (I would definitely come back for more every other week)! Make sure you take advantage of their location and visit the museum after your meal.
You wont regret visiting and having dinner
Delightful food situated in the MCA. Great cocktail list
Similar to modern art, don't worry about getting it. Or in this case liking the food. It's about the experience eating in the MCA. Be open, and see if the food makes you react emotionally.
One of my favorite places for brunch when in the city! The donuts are always incredible and the French toast was delicious! Looking forward to coming back soon!

What an amazing restaurant! This is my first time visiting. Service staff is so engaging and thoughtful. Restaurant space is a little sparse, but not off putting. The manager, Lauren, stopped by to check on us more than once and I felt like she was hosting me at her home. So pleasant. Regarding the food... we ordered the Green Shakshuka and the Pork cheek ragout. Best meal we have had on our vacation. I wish we lived closer so that we could visit here regularly.

We made reservations to have a nice dinner here. We live a few blocks away and heard good things. We ended up leaving after drinks. The space is loud and it feels like you're in a weird, corner hallway space in an arena, like the UC. Odd spot for a expensive restaurant when there are so many quality options out there.
Food is not that great
great food went during lunch, little long getting food ordered
Food and service excellent, unique flavors that are priced accordingly.
A delightful experience. We went for drag queen brunch. The food was unique and delicious. This experience was a perfect compliment to the MCA.
The vibe was great, the staff were delightful, and the food was satisfactory. The menu seemed as though it tried a little hard. Well worth the visit, the staff made it.

Edit:  i was drying my hands when I saw an employee of the Marisol leaving the restrooms without washing his hands. He just went back to...the restaurant preparing the tables for dinner before the opening. I was shocked and mad by what i just saw. I immediately talked to the manager to complain about that and ask her to change all the dinning set on the tables. This is the best way to spread germs, bacteria and to be sick, disgusting!!  8 months ago: Several fresh and veggie starters are available and very few for main meal, desert menu looked very good but didn t take one. It s not a "wow" but it s good. Price is regular for such location. Staff is taking care of customers, place is not really quiet but it s not noisy either. Nice restrooms though.

Great experience, I was there with my colleagues. Its an upscale arty place with good selection of food. The spread is different and has a great variety to chose from with great service. They have Orange Wine and much more. Their drinks and food goes well for a office get together small family gatherings in heart of Chicago, very close to downtown.
Great space, good food and friendly staff. Oh and there is a museum :)
Good drinks
From the fantastic (and creative) food to the service staff that truly all love what they do, this is a hidden jewel in the North Loop. Next time, we're making a day of it with the museum.
Holy cow. The gravlax brunch is spectacular. What can I say.  Staff is friendly yet professional.  Too bad I live in Northeast otherwise I'd come and visit this place more often.
Nice place
Veggie burger was incredible.
(Translated by Google) Rich, original and excellent service.  (Original) Rico, original y excelente servicio.
Food and service were impeccable. Staff was exceptional with my ailing dad who happened to be full of dad-jokes.

Ordered a sandwich to go from the counter & it was wildly overpriced -$15 + tip for a small turkey sandwich w/o any sides such as chips, pickle, or a small salad. Quality is good-value for money is not. The bialy, on the other hand, is incredible, and definitely worth $5. They serve Metric coffee which is a plus. Service is hit or miss.
I love this place so much! Really incredible food in such a great space. Service was excellent. Can’t wait to go back.

It is cold indoor. One feels uncomfortable and wonders why the management insists in keeping air conditioning on when it's cold outside. Food is very nice but the service is slow and disorganized. We forgive them bec they're young and the food is good. The Marisol salad is excellent, the hummus very good, the wagyu beef tartare is not wagyu (nowadays it simply takes a white collar to turn beef into wagyu beef). The restaurant is nice, with an elegant touch. You feel you're in a museum. Balancing all aspects, let's say 4 stars.

Fantastic place for breakfast or brunch. We came with friends and easily found a table on Sunday morning. The place is also family friendly. Aside from that, their menu had all sorts of deliciousness and I'd totally recommend their breakfast burrito, salmon bagel, and potatoes as a side. Our servers were great - attentive, quick, friendly. Everything was reasonably priced. Lastly, the restaurant is simply beautiful and nicely decorated inside which makes it a great place to eat out and enjoy your time. Finding parking was also easy thanks to a valet garage right across the street.
Tasty breakfast, could've skipped the museum

Mixed review. Food was excellent. Decor and revamp a complete let down. Nobody wants to eat in a student canteen. Service was mixed... if you are going to have students serve food at least have them clean their shoes and wear a bra before service. This place needs help on how to position service, perception and price.
One of my favorite restaurants in Chicago.  Great atmosphere, amazing people, and the best food.
Extraordinary place for Chicago! Taste and dish serving are really stand out!
Thoughtful food, well prepared and seasonally fresh

LOVE the new menu - 8 oz trout topped with rice, blood orange, and carrot. The creativity and the sum taste of all these ingredients make it special and delicious. Goes well with the while wine.  A big plus is definitely their service ! Follow instagram @liying_chou
Everything we've had there is great. Really like their sunflower seed hummus. The two sorbets today we're amazing. The staff was very friendly, knowledgeable and helpful.
Delicious
Very interesting menu. Tasty food. Lively setting. Really a nice surprise.
Great spot!
A great place with great food and nice people with a perfect service! Loved it and highly recommend it!
A bit on the spendy side but great wine and nice service regardless. Better than most food you'll find in that area especially.
The food is surprisingly good! Love the fried potatoes!
Delicious, creative dishes with many vegetarian options
If you like Lula, but own far too few plaids...

It's cute addition to a museum. The had a different cider on draft than what most bars carry that wasn't bad at all. Bartender did, however, leave a friend of ours hanging on her drink for about 10 mins or so it seemed. A cute place to catch up with friends after seeing some exhibits, installations, speeches, talks, and so forth it seems.
Burrata was bomb

I truly liked this dining establishment, the food is amazing, plus the shower rooms were tidy. It was a little cold indoors, so yeah, it was not the very best. The food serve is good as well. I will most definitely consider going back again if I ever land the opportunity. Me and also my pal purchased the combo and also we were not let down. My one tip is to maintain the cold exterior. Cheers!
We were so surprised how much we loved it ! Every dish was special and delicious.
Inventive, fun atmosphere, great service, not overpriced.
The coffee and grilled cheese sandwich I ordered didn't agree with me.
Came for the brunch, stayed for the art!

Sitting facing the private dining room. Between the sea and sky of Chris Ofili's black line mural. Looking through the legs of lowered peacock feathers to a sea maidens grotto. And the best pasta I recall ever tasting. Unmissable.
Nice room, good service.
I thought I would not enjoy the place, but I was hungry. The food was great! The wait staff was polite and attentive.

Excellent place to try out unique and delicious food preparations. Plenty of options for vegetarians (I am a vegetarian myself), and priced reasonably for the quality of food they deliver. Service is excellent, with humble and thoughtful servers. Food is comparable to that from Michelin star restaurants, and you will be surprised by what you get. A must try place if you are in Chicago.

My girlfriend and I had an excellent dinner here on a Tuesday night. The atmosphere was casual upscale, music selection was a fun jazz.  We went with the sunflower hummus for an appetizer, which was particularly phenomenal. I went with the buccatini - delicious and appropriately sized. My girlfriend's elote was tasty too, though we think it would have served better in a small portion size as an appetizer. Overall, a great experience, and we will definitely return.

(Translated by Google) Certainly good quality of food, self service but good service and attentive and attentive waiters, a bit aseptic and impersonal environment  (Original) Sicuramente buona la qualità del cibo, self service ma servizio buono e camerieri solleciti e attenti, un po' asettico e impersonale l'ambiente
It is my name
Excellent food and atmosphere.
Excellent coffee, gorgeous space to sit and enjoy
Very good idea to host such an original and well presented menu.
The food is fantastic and very different. Many vegetarian options.

Had a great time here for dinner.  I thought at first it might be a little touristy considering the location, but in actuality it seemed filled with locals just leaving work.  The food was excellent, and I really liked the ambiance.  Much better than I expected for being inside a museum.  Great place.
Excellent excellent food and hospitality. Unlike anything you've ever had before. Incredible and worth every cent.
Great food, service, ambiance, everything!

Amazing place!! Must visit restaurants in Chicago! I cannot stress how awesome this place is. The flax seed crackers and sunflower hummus and the kampachi tartare blew me away. They use flavor combinations that you will not expect and make some remarkable tasty food with it. One of the best restaurants I have ever been to. It is situated inside the museum of contemporary art and is perfect for a great dinner after touring the restaurant during the day. Try anything on their menu that seems interesting and I guarantee you will not be disappointed.
Get the breakfast burrito and add sausage, you won’t be disappointed.
Great coffee, directly in the museum. (Didn't have any food, cannot comment).
always spot on, from the the drinks, to the food, to the staff

Pretty good food, really nice atmosphere. It's actually inside the MCA, which can throw some people off.  They do a brunch, but it's only so-so in my opinion. There's a Wildberry next door (a spin-off location) and if you get tired of waiting in line for breakfast there, you can always come here.  Their lunch is much better though and if you're in the museum and get hungry, you're not wasting your money. It's worth eating at.

We ate in time for the brunch menu. The food was incredible, and the use of spices and flavor combinations was excellent! From the food to the coffee, everything was fantastic. I'll be making reservations for the next time I come to the MCA!

So far, I’ve been once for dinner and once for happy hour drinks. Both have been very pleasant experiences. Nice short menu with a decent variety of options. Their bar menu is fantastic and the bar tenders are happy to give recommendations. Highly recommend a reservation for lunch, but easy to saddle up to the bar in the evening. Nice hidden gem in this neighborhood!
Good place

We were excited to see that the MCA added a restaurant to the mix. We had a blueberry muffin and  two lattes. Made fresh we could also tell the milk was high quality. It satisfied our coffee craving and the cute milk designs made for a little extra cuteness. We hope to try more food on our next visit.
Nice restaurant but they need to highlight Chef Shara food more she a really good cook
Excellent.  Musuems have the best little restaurants throughout the world

(Translated by Google) Awesome dish with salmon. Perfect roast. Not overdried, but with a crisp. Highly recommend!  (Original) Офигенное блюдо с лососем. Идеальная прожарка. Не пересушено, но с хрустящей корочкой. Очень рекомендую!
Nice place, it was quite busy. I only tried a cappuccino there - it was really good. I would like to come back to try more!
Loved brunch...and what better way to spend the afternoon strolling around the museum...or just drinking lattes and their version of mimosa...
Great service and special food. Tasty!

Love what they with the space in the mca. Feels like im at an airport with the on the go cafe then the dinning in space, lol. The pairing of the Chefs and Menu at Marisol with the Mca is like bread and butter. Light art and a Hip vibe surrounds the dinning room. We had a Short wait past our reservation time and service slightly uninterested but that never stops me from enjoying my meal. We came for Brunch and left giddy with satisfaction. Our Dishes were Sensory Overload. Excited, anxious, a tad bit bent off the lula bloody marys, intrigued by the flavors falling deep into a food coma then brought back to life with a Cappuccino. Twas awesome. Im a fan.  Oh and you might have to park in the garage not too much free or meter parking around.
The best ham and cheese sandwich with perfect touch of sweetness from date honey.  I don't know what dressing came on the side salad, but it was surprisingly really good.

Heard great things about this place and was excited to try it out.  We came for Sunday brunch and the place was busy.  I definitely recommend a reservation.  Service was great. We got seated and served right away.  We had the steak and eggs, duck confit , buttermilk pancakes, pqm bacon and a side of scrambled eggs.  Every dish was delicious but we could not stop eating the pancakes it was divine.
Excellent!

One of the best spots in Chicago - make sure to try the burrito - it’s veggie and really good. The deserts are really good as well. Just about everything... and it’s light not too heavy. Clearly you can tell I like this place plus it’s right under the Museum of Contemporary Art. Win win 🙌🏽
The combinations were strange but tasted fantastic
The best brunch egg burrito at a non-Hispanic restaurant. Service can be slow but quality makes up for it.

They may have only opened yesterday, but the staff at Marisol know their stuff. Delicious dishes with fresh ingredients combined to highlight vibrant flavors. Great service and a wonderful way to spend a Friday evening.
Thoughtful concepts behind beautiful dishes in an amazing dinning environment. Highly recommended!

(Translated by Google) It is a good place to eat with your family, friends or colleagues, I totally recommend it since there are varieties of very rich dishes, this place is spacious, that is good and there is also a good atmosphere.  (Original) es un buen lugar para comer con tu familia, amigos u compañeros, se los recomiendo totalmente ya que hay variedades de platos muy  ricos, este lugar es amplio eso es bueno y tambien hay un buen ambiente.

While visiting the MCA from out of town, we stumbled across this restaurant on its second day of operation. We lucked out. The food was some of the best I've had, and the highlight of our weekend. Service was perfect and dessert was excellent. The plates are designed to be shared, and our meal of fried quail, salad, and summer squash was just right for two people.
